ity=3D"high" decoding=3D"async" class=3D"alignnone size-full wp-image-6160"=
 data-src=3D"http://www.natgeokids.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Zombie-ap=
ocalypse-survival-2.jpg" alt=3D"zombie apocalypse survival" width=3D"635" h=
eight=3D"404" data-srcset=3D"https://cdn.creatureandcoagency.com/uploads/20=
16/11/Zombie-apocalypse-survival-2.jpg 635w, https://cdn.creatureandcoagenc=
y.com/uploads/2016/11/Zombie-apocalypse-survival-2-300x191.jpg 300w" data-s=
izes=3D"(max-width: 635px) 100vw, 635px"></a></p>
<p><strong>It=E2=80=99s the end of the world. What can&nbsp;<em>you</em> do=
 to survive?</strong></p>
<p><span class=3D"s1">We spoke to&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"s2">an astrobi=
ologist about the survival science needed to keep you alive, should you fin=
d yourself facing the end of the world, or worse, a herd of&nbsp;<em>zombie=
s</em>=E2=80=A6</span></p>
<p>Okay=E2=80=A6 so it=E2=80=99s unlikely to happen, but it=E2=80=99s a fun=
 way to picture all the different skills we=E2=80=99d need to survive.</p>
<p>Where would you go? What would you take with you? Would you have the ski=
lls needed to rebuild civilisation?</p>
<p>These are the questions <strong>Dr Lewis Dartnell</strong>, an <strong>a=
strobiologist</strong> (someone who studies how life can survive in differe=
nt environments) will be answering at this year=E2=80=99s <strong><a href=
=3D"https://www.thebigbangfair.co.uk/" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"nofollow">B=
ig Bang Fair</a></strong>, which<strong>&nbsp;</strong>encourages young peo=
ple to learn about science, technology, engineering and maths (STEM).</p>
<p>Check out his top tips on how to survive should you find yourself facing=
 the end of the world=E2=80=A6</p>
<h1>1. Know your survival skills</h1>
<p><a href=3D"http://www.natgeokids.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Zombie-a=
pocalypse-survival-1.jpg"><img data-lazyloaded=3D"1" src=3D"data:image/gif;=
base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" decoding=
=3D"async" class=3D"alignnone size-full wp-image-6159" data-src=3D"http://w=
ww.natgeokids.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Zombie-apocalypse-survival-1.j=
pg" alt=3D"zombie apocalypse survival" width=3D"635" height=3D"404" data-sr=
cset=3D"https://cdn.creatureandcoagency.com/uploads/2016/11/Zombie-apocalyp=
se-survival-1.jpg 635w, https://cdn.creatureandcoagency.com/uploads/2016/11=
/Zombie-apocalypse-survival-1-300x191.jpg 300w" data-sizes=3D"(max-width: 6=
35px) 100vw, 635px"></a></p>
<p>=E2=80=9CImagine you found yourself in a post-apocalyptic wasteland, how=
 do you keep yourself alive? Well, there are loads of everyday objects that=
 could help you in an emergency situation.</p>
<p>=E2=80=9CA fire alarm for example, can actually be used to <em>start</em=
> a fire, and a humble plastic bottle can be used to sterilise drinking wat=
er. Simply fill your bottle, and leave it out in the sunshine. The sun=E2=
=80=99s UV rays will pass right through the water and kill any germs that a=
re in there.</p>
<p>=E2=80=9CYou can even make a simple gas-fire stove out of tin cans, whic=
h is really efficient. It uses the same process (called gasification) that =
was used to power cars across Europe during the <a href=3D"https://www.natg=
eokids.com/history/world-war-two" target=3D"_blank">Second World War</a>!</=
p>
<p>=E2=80=9CAnd how about opening a tin can without any tools? Easy, there=
=E2=80=99s a trick for that! You=E2=80=99ll need to turn the can upside dow=
n, so it can get a little messy, but it=E2=80=99s handy!=E2=80=9D</p>
<h1>2. Choose a good hideout</h1>
<p><a href=3D"http://www.natgeokids.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Zombie-a=
pocalypse-survival-5.jpg"><img data-lazyloaded=3D"1" src=3D"data:image/gif;=
base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" decoding=
=3D"async" class=3D"alignnone size-full wp-image-6164" data-src=3D"http://w=
ww.natgeokids.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Zombie-apocalypse-survival-5.j=
pg" alt=3D"zombie apocalypse survival" width=3D"635" height=3D"404" data-sr=
cset=3D"https://cdn.creatureandcoagency.com/uploads/2016/11/Zombie-apocalyp=
se-survival-5.jpg 635w, https://cdn.creatureandcoagency.com/uploads/2016/11=
/Zombie-apocalypse-survival-5-300x191.jpg 300w" data-sizes=3D"(max-width: 6=
35px) 100vw, 635px"></a></p>
<p><span class=3D"s1">=E2=80=9CFirstly, get out of the cities. A lot of us =
live in cities nowadays as they=E2=80=99re so convenient and full of shops,=
 but if civilisation collapsed and you had to do things for yourself, the c=
ity is one of the worst places to be. What if there=E2=80=99s no electricit=
y, no gas, no running water, no lights, heating, and you can=E2=80=99t grow=
 your own food because everything=E2=80=99s covered in tarmac? You=E2=80=99=
ll want to escape to the countryside! Find a spot near a river with fresh w=
ater you can drink, and start learning how to grow your own food.</span></p=
>
<p><span class=3D"s1">=E2=80=9CThe Lake District would be ideal. Just make =
sure you avoid the Arctic circle or the middle of a desert!=E2=80=9D</span>=
</p>
<h1>3. Pack a survival kit</h1>
<p><span class=3D"s1">=E2=80=9CImagine you=E2=80=99ve got a four-minute war=
ning to get out of the house.</span>&nbsp;Grab some fresh water and cans of=
 food =E2=80=93 if you forget your can-opener, don=E2=80=99t worry because =
you now know how to open one without! =E2=80=93 a knife, twine for tying th=
ings, or failing that, use your iPod headphones instead! And don=E2=80=99t =
forget that empty plastic bottle for sterilising water. It=E2=80=99s all ab=
out being clever, ingenious and using things in new ways.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p><span class=3D"s1">=E2=80=9CAccording to recent research, o</span>ver a =
third of the UK population (36%) are already prepared and keep a =E2=80=9Cb=
ug-out bag=E2=80=99 (a kit that=E2=80=99ll keep you alive for 72 hours!) re=
ady in case disaster strikes!=E2=80=9D</p>
<h1>4. <em>Use</em> your mobile phone</h1>
<p><a href=3D"http://www.natgeokids.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Zombie-a=
pocalypse-survival.jpg"><img data-lazyloaded=3D"1" src=3D"data:image/gif;ba=
se64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" decoding=3D"=
async" class=3D"alignnone size-full wp-image-6165" data-src=3D"http://www.n=
atgeokids.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Zombie-apocalypse-survival.jpg" al=
t=3D"zombie apocalypse survival" width=3D"635" height=3D"404" data-srcset=
=3D"https://cdn.creatureandcoagency.com/uploads/2016/11/Zombie-apocalypse-s=
urvival.jpg 635w, https://cdn.creatureandcoagency.com/uploads/2016/11/Zombi=
e-apocalypse-survival-300x191.jpg 300w" data-sizes=3D"(max-width: 635px) 10=
0vw, 635px"></a></p>
<p><span class=3D"s1">=E2=80=9CThe one thing we all can=E2=80=99t live with=
out these days are our mobile phones, but if civilisation collapsed they=E2=
=80=99d not be much use at all. However, there is <em>one</em> feature on y=
our mobile that will continue working for at least a couple of months, and =
that=E2=80=99s GPS. I estimate we=E2=80=99ve got about six months of life i=
n the satellites should they be abandoned, so while you won=E2=80=99t be ab=
le to phone people or =E2=80=98<a href=3D"https://twitter.com/NGKidsUK" tar=
get=3D"_blank">tweet</a>=E2=80=99 for help, the map function will continue =
working as it relies on satellite signals and not the mobile phone network =
=E2=80=93 that goes for your smartphone compass, too!=E2=80=9D</span></p>
<h1>5. Become a super scavenger</h1>
<p><a href=3D"http://www.natgeokids.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Zombie-a=
pocalypse-survival-4.jpg"><img data-lazyloaded=3D"1" src=3D"data:image/gif;=
base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" decoding=
=3D"async" class=3D"alignnone size-full wp-image-6162" data-src=3D"http://w=
ww.natgeokids.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Zombie-apocalypse-survival-4.j=
pg" alt=3D"zombie apocalypse survival" width=3D"635" height=3D"404" data-sr=
cset=3D"https://cdn.creatureandcoagency.com/uploads/2016/11/Zombie-apocalyp=
se-survival-4.jpg 635w, https://cdn.creatureandcoagency.com/uploads/2016/11=
/Zombie-apocalypse-survival-4-300x191.jpg 300w" data-sizes=3D"(max-width: 6=
35px) 100vw, 635px"></a></p>
<p>=E2=80=9CThe biggest key to surviving is learning how to scavenge and fo=
rage for the things you need. One of the best things to get your hands on i=
s a car battery and alternator. Use them to make a simple windmill or a wat=
ermill to recharge the battery. A scaveneged solar panel can be used to cha=
rge your mobile phone.</p>
<p>=E2=80=9CAnd if you=E2=80=99re in need of a compass, an analog wristwatc=
h will do just as good a job. Simply point the minute hand towards the sun =
and halfway between the number 12 and the hour hand will show you where sou=
th is!=E2=80=9D</p>
<h1>6. Gather a useful gang</h1>
<p>=E2=80=9CYou might have imagined who you=E2=80=99d take with you during =
an apocolypse. Who=E2=80=99d be most useful? Do you know anyone who owns an=
 allotment, who has the skills to grow their own food? Or someone who=E2=80=
=99s good with their hands, like a carpenter or metal worker, or good at fi=
xing things, like a car mechanic? These are the people that will be most us=
eful when you=E2=80=99re trying to rebuild society. People like computer pr=
ogrammers or astrobiologists (like me!) will probably have to learn a few m=
ore useful skills!=E2=80=9D</p>
<h1>7. And what about a <em>zombie</em> apocalypse=E2=80=A6?</h1>
<p><a href=3D"http://www.natgeokids.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Zombie-a=
pocalypse-survival-3.jpg"><img data-lazyloaded=3D"1" src=3D"data:image/gif;=
base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" decoding=
=3D"async" class=3D"alignnone size-full wp-image-6161" data-src=3D"http://w=
ww.natgeokids.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Zombie-apocalypse-survival-3.j=
pg" alt=3D"zombie apocalypse survival" width=3D"635" height=3D"404" data-sr=
cset=3D"https://cdn.creatureandcoagency.com/uploads/2016/11/Zombie-apocalyp=
se-survival-3.jpg 635w, https://cdn.creatureandcoagency.com/uploads/2016/11=
/Zombie-apocalypse-survival-3-300x191.jpg 300w" data-sizes=3D"(max-width: 6=
35px) 100vw, 635px"></a></p>
<p><span class=3D"s1">=E2=80=9COne of the safest locations during a zombie =
apocalypse (not that that=E2=80=99s ever going to happen!) would be a priso=
n. With their high walls and barbed wire fences, they=E2=80=99re great at k=
eeping people in, but of course, they=E2=80=99re also great at keeping peop=
le <em>out</em>. Find one with its own water supply and a stock pile of foo=
d, dig up the car park to plant crops, and you=E2=80=99ve got an extremely =
safe refuge!=E2=80=9D</span></p>
